									<header class="major">
										<h2>About me</h2>
									</header>
											

<p><span class="image right"><img src="images/trung.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="350"  /></span>I am a first-year graduate student at the <a href="http://www.math.utah.edu/">University of Utah</a> studying commutative algebra. My research interests lie in commutative algebra, homological algebra and algebraic topology. Particularly, I am interested in the relation between the functors Ext, Tor and free, injective resolutions of modules over Noetherian rings.
</p>

<p>I am from Vietnam and obtained my Bachelor in Mathematics at the <a href="https://web.hcmus.edu.vn/en/">University of Science, Vietnam National Univerisity, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam</a>, before moving to Salt Lake City. Here is a little bit about me: I can speak Vietnamese fluently. "I make jokes when I'm uncomfortable". I have been in 4 states of America. I am an avid movie-goers and a big fan of sitcoms and would love to talk about them.</p>

<p>Here is my <a href="files/CV.pdf">CV</a>, updated November 2018.	</p>	

